            <fr:title text="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations">Reflexive-transitive closure of <fr:em>finite</fr:em> <fr:link href="jms-00JF.xml" title="Path in a directed graph" addr="jms-00JF" type="local">endo-relations</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Observation</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>In the case of an <fr:link href="jms-00JF.xml" title="Path in a directed graph" addr="jms-00JF" type="local">endo-relation</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link href="jms-00JH.xml" title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation" addr="jms-00JH" type="local">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *}]]></fr:tex> can be computed using a finite union rather over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m \leq  n]]></fr:tex> rather than an infinite union over all of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>; in particular, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k \leq  n} R^{\circ  k}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7049</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6021</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6021.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>There are only <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> distinct elements that could be related, so there cannot be a chain of distinct elements with length <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[o>n]]></fr:tex>, and any finite path in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> can be replaced by one that has no repetitions.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
